       "\"I've been attending this religious study group, and it's given me a chance to express my thoughts freely without fear of judgment or reprisal. Even though I'm the only one in the room who holds these views, I find it helpful to practice articulating my ideas. In my childhood home and with my relatives, I was always careful not to stray too far from the accepted beliefs. But deep down, I've always felt more comfortable with my natural inclinations. I'd like to work on asserting myself more in various situations, not just this one, so that I don't feel as awkward when I'm expressing my thoughts.\""
